<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Netflix uses Chaos Engineering, specifically through their tool known as Chaos Monkey, to enhance the resilience and reliability of their systems, ensuring a seamless streaming experience for users worldwide. Chaos Engineering involves injecting controlled chaos into systems to identify and address potential weaknesses. Chaos Monkey plays a central role in this process by randomly terminating instances in Netflix's production environment. This simulation of real-world failures allows engineers to observe how systems respond and to improve fault tolerance. By embracing the unpredictability of failures, Netflix engineers are able to strengthen their architecture, ensuring that it can handle disruptions gracefully and maintain uninterrupted service for users. This approach to system design not only improves reliability but also prepares the infrastructure to withstand and quickly recover from unforeseen challenges. #tech #technology #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/owlKaVIIECgNd7peXKLSS7TfrzYcBIAeGCFjAP?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=W6N%2FjoAVSE7KFN6HQiSWv%2FBPaLY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/owlKaVIIECgNd7peXKLSS7TfrzYcBIAeGCFjAP?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=W6N%2FjoAVSE7KFN6HQiSWv%2FBPaLY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/owlKaVIIECgNd7peXKLSS7TfrzYcBIAeGCFjAP?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=W6N%2FjoAVSE7KFN6HQiSWv%2FBPaLY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Why dont hackers just shut down the entire internet?! There are two critical systems that, if compromised, could cause massive disruptions: BGP and DNS. BGP, is like the internet's traffic control system. It decides how data is routed across the globe. In 2022, a BGP mishap actually rerouted a large chunk of European mobile internet traffic to China! While not a deliberate attack, it shows how BGP vulnerabilities can cause widespread issues. Then there's DNS. Think of it as the internet's phonebook. In 2016, an attack on Dyn's DNS servers took down major websites across the US for hours. But here's where it gets interesting. While hackers might struggle to &quot;shut down&quot; the internet globally, governments have managed to do it on a national scale. During the Arab Spring, Egypt effectively turned off internet access for its citizens. China's Great Firewall is another example, filtering web content nationwide. These government-level shutdowns often work by interfering with critical services or controlling the physical infrastructure connecting to the global network. They can make the internet appear broken, even if the underlying connection still exists. A global internet shutdown by hackers is unlikely thanks to the network's decentralized nature, localized or national disruptions are a real concern.  #tech #technology #stem #techexplained #techtok " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/928fb939451042158fe1ba1b8470804c_1724888327?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=vuK3v6jdpwB13fnrIAofZ6BTZj0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/928fb939451042158fe1ba1b8470804c_1724888327?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=vuK3v6jdpwB13fnrIAofZ6BTZj0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/928fb939451042158fe1ba1b8470804c_1724888327?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=vuK3v6jdpwB13fnrIAofZ6BTZj0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ How does cloud storage keep expanding?! I havenâ€™t deleted anything since 2010!  When you upload a file to cloud storage, your device first chunks the file into smaller pieces. These chunks are then sent over the internet using HTTPS to the cloud provider's servers. Upon receipt, the data center's load balancer directs the incoming chunks to available storage servers. The file is reassembled, and its metadata (like filename, size, and owner) is recorded in a distributed database. The file is then encrypted using a method like AES-256 and stored across multiple physical devices for redundancy. A unique identifier for the file is generated and sent back to your device. Simultaneously, the storage system updates its distributed file table, making the file quickly accessible from any connected device. If the file already exists, deduplication algorithms may prevent storing duplicate data, instead just updating metadata to link your account to the existing file. This entire process, from upload initiation to confirmation, typically occurs within seconds, leveraging high-speed networks and optimized data handling protocols. #tech #technology #coding #stem #techtok " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/1686cb228e6746de894a9d240249c0a1_1724880845?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=oQcuVMPbXsjYn0lMiRQdxOCdtb8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/1686cb228e6746de894a9d240249c0a1_1724880845?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=oQcuVMPbXsjYn0lMiRQdxOCdtb8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/1686cb228e6746de894a9d240249c0a1_1724880845?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=oQcuVMPbXsjYn0lMiRQdxOCdtb8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Is Telegram really the most secure messaging app?!  When a user sends a message on Telegram, the app immediately encrypts it on their device using the MTProto protocol. For secret chats, this encryption is end-to-end, meaning only the intended recipient can decrypt it. The encrypted message then travels through Telegram's distributed network of servers, which are spread across various countries to enhance security. As the message moves, it benefits from perfect forward secrecy, ensuring that even if future encryption keys are compromised, past messages remain secure. The message arrives at the recipient's device, where it's decrypted and displayed. If it's a self-destructing message, it will vanish after the set time. Throughout this process, Telegram's open-source client code allows for independent security verification, while features like two-step verification and the absence of cloud backups add extra layers of protection.  #tech #technology #stem #coding " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/0f596c20ddda4d4aaf1b75e570b88aa2_1724447510?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=MyRu%2Fsnuu%2B1s5V3TIJEJ70eutu4%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/0f596c20ddda4d4aaf1b75e570b88aa2_1724447510?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=MyRu%2Fsnuu%2B1s5V3TIJEJ70eutu4%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/0f596c20ddda4d4aaf1b75e570b88aa2_1724447510?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=MyRu%2Fsnuu%2B1s5V3TIJEJ70eutu4%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ How come Face ID never mistakes you?  Have you ever wondered how is face ID able to recognize you whether you have glasses, a beard, or completely change up your look? But yet it never mistakes you for someone else, you can never unlock someone else's phone. Now, face I.D. doesn't just store one single image of your face, but rather continually updates and learns every single time you unlock your phone. And this allows it to adapt to gradual changes over time. The system is designed to recognize depth and contours rather than surface level details, so it's less affected by things such as facial hair or glasses. It also focuses on stable features of your face, things such as the distance between your eyes, the height of your cheekbones, things that don't change that much. Even when you put on glasses or have a beard. Moreover, face ID uses something called partial matching and can store multiple appearances for a single user. So even if you do grow a beard, color your hair or change up your appearance, it might create an alternate appearance while still retaining data from the original. And it's this combination of 3D technology, machine learning and adaptive design that allows face ID to be extremely accurate. So accurate to the point that even twins can't unlock each other's phones. Most of the time. #tech #technology #stem #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/o4eGRlqZmEJYECBqUBxF6DHEIuDBNxAQEQfTdv?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=VJbsPNK1n%2Frt%2Be8hXJP4T%2FWRs%2BE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/o4eGRlqZmEJYECBqUBxF6DHEIuDBNxAQEQfTdv?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=VJbsPNK1n%2Frt%2Be8hXJP4T%2FWRs%2BE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/o4eGRlqZmEJYECBqUBxF6DHEIuDBNxAQEQfTdv?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=VJbsPNK1n%2Frt%2Be8hXJP4T%2FWRs%2BE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Why isnt there alwaya free wifi on planes?!  The lack of free Wi-Fi on airplanes in 2024 is due to both financial incentives for airlines and technical limitations. To offer Wi-Fi, planes require antennas, a network modem, and wireless access points, with retrofitting existing aircraft being expensive and time-consuming. Wi-Fi connectivity is achieved either through satellite antennas or air-to-ground (ATG) antennas. ATG antennas face challenges over large bodies of water, leading to reliance on satellite Wi-Fi, which uses orbiting satellites for data transmission, ensuring continuous connectivity. Airlines often use a hybrid of both systems. While charging for Wi-Fi does generate extra revenue for airlines, it also manages bandwidth limitations. With potentially hundreds of passengers wanting to use the service, making it free would overwhelm the limited bandwidth, degrading the quality for everyone. Hence, airlines charge for Wi-Fi to limit the number of users and maintain service quality. #tech #stem #technology #techexplained #techexpert " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oQeifwVAFCEIl8AspxGfkaQCfIyXZ7GQ9LMRlN?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=fioBoLFz6yOUVnSDZjnvoJhtW94%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oQeifwVAFCEIl8AspxGfkaQCfIyXZ7GQ9LMRlN?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=fioBoLFz6yOUVnSDZjnvoJhtW94%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oQeifwVAFCEIl8AspxGfkaQCfIyXZ7GQ9LMRlN?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=fioBoLFz6yOUVnSDZjnvoJhtW94%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Why does Google Maps never get you lost?  OK maybe it does sometimes but this is pretty cool bow the tech works.  Google Maps never gets you lost thanks to a complex system of technologies. It starts with a massive geospatial database, but static maps aren't enough.  Therefore, it collects real-time data from millions of devices, feeding machine learning models for traffic prediction. But accurate navigation needs more than just predictions. Therefore, Google employs the A* search algorithm, an efficient pathfinding method that finds the optimal route by evaluating both the distance traveled and the estimated distance to the goal.  This algorithm works on a graph of the road network, with edges weighted by current and predicted travel times. But even the best route is useless without knowing where you are.  Therefore, Google fuses data from GPS, Wi-Fi, cellular networks, and device sensors for precise localization. Finally, map-matching algorithms ensure you always appear on the correct road. All this happens in milliseconds, leveraging Google's global network of data centers, to keep you on track no matter where you're headed. #tech #technology #developer #stem #techexpert #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/eb6c5e948a20455b86f39f9aaf5eee9d_1723322851?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=mlkUPDlMZHIByV8%2FLSjrkJud9rc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/eb6c5e948a20455b86f39f9aaf5eee9d_1723322851?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=mlkUPDlMZHIByV8%2FLSjrkJud9rc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/eb6c5e948a20455b86f39f9aaf5eee9d_1723322851?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=mlkUPDlMZHIByV8%2FLSjrkJud9rc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What was the first high-level programming language? While there were many programming languages that came before this... here is the first high-level one!  Fortran (Formula Translation) is widely recognized as the first high-level programming language to achieve widespread use. Developed by a team at IBM led by John Backus, Fortran was first released in 1957. It marked a significant leap forward in programming technology, allowing scientists and engineers to write complex mathematical formulas in a way that was much closer to standard mathematical notation than previous assembly languages. This made it considerably easier for non-specialists to write programs, greatly expanding the pool of potential programmers.  #tech #technology #coding #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oUZzBGdVElEEUrhEu0PQ1QgOniAAniBBy9SIr?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=6wmJ%2FWQgMfySf%2B%2F31x%2FOZIu0z94%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oUZzBGdVElEEUrhEu0PQ1QgOniAAniBBy9SIr?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=6wmJ%2FWQgMfySf%2B%2F31x%2FOZIu0z94%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oUZzBGdVElEEUrhEu0PQ1QgOniAAniBBy9SIr?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=6wmJ%2FWQgMfySf%2B%2F31x%2FOZIu0z94%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Palali Music çš„ sonido original åˆ›ä½œçš„ What is the difference between OAuth and JWT?  OAuth and JWT are both used in authentication processes, but they serve different purposes. OAuth is an authorization framework that allows third-party applications to access user resources without sharing credentials, often used when one service needs to access data from another on behalf of a user. JWT, or JSON Web Token, is like a secure digital ID card for computers. It's a compact way to securely transmit information about a user between parties as a JSON object. When you log in, instead of checking your credentials every time, the server gives you a JWT containing information about your identity and permissions. This token has three parts: a header, a payload with claims about you, and a signature to ensure it hasn't been tampered with. You send this token with each request, allowing the server to quickly verify who you are without constant database lookups. In a real-world scenario, a photo printing service might use OAuth to access a user's Google Photos for printing, while using JWT to manage the user's session within its own application. The choice between them depends on the specific authentication and authorization needs of the application. #tech #technology #developer #stem #education " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMmGJDyvhBeEqAFRzB6I2r4BQsE2QPfGDmqDEj?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=qbc0FixPlURa77XeVClkEWWOBOQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMmGJDyvhBeEqAFRzB6I2r4BQsE2QPfGDmqDEj?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=qbc0FixPlURa77XeVClkEWWOBOQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMmGJDyvhBeEqAFRzB6I2r4BQsE2QPfGDmqDEj?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=qbc0FixPlURa77XeVClkEWWOBOQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ James Jones çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ I had no idea Google was originally named that ðŸ¤£ 1. Email was created before the World Wide Web (WWW): Email was invented in 1971 by Ray Tomlinson, nearly two decades before the World Wide Web. It was designed as a way to send messages between computers on ARPANET, the precursor to the modern internet. The WWW, on the other hand, was created by Tim Berners-Lee in 1989 and became publicly available in 1991.  2. The original name for the search engine Google was BackRub:  In 1996, when Larry Page and Sergey Brin began developing their search engine at Stanford University, they called it &quot;BackRub.&quot; This name was chosen because the system checked backlinks to estimate the importance of a site. The project was renamed &quot;Google&quot; in 1997, a play on the mathematical term &quot;googol&quot; (1 followed by 100 zeros). 3. The first text message ever sent was &quot;Merry Christmas&quot; in 1992: On December 3, 1992, Neil Papworth, a 22-year-old software programmer, sent the first SMS text message from a computer to a mobile phone. The recipient was Richard Jarvis, a director at Vodafon #tech #technology #developer #stem #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/c6607996f9f74001861bdf81101394c1_1722799918?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=LQ%2BtmygyFmupxWeNnYP75VL%2BQl8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/c6607996f9f74001861bdf81101394c1_1722799918?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=LQ%2BtmygyFmupxWeNnYP75VL%2BQl8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/c6607996f9f74001861bdf81101394c1_1722799918?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=LQ%2BtmygyFmupxWeNnYP75VL%2BQl8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Why does X never crash during major world events when everyone is tweeting?  Okay there have been a few times it has crashed but here is why it typically can handle so many tweets.  X's ability to handle major world events stems from its sophisticated infrastructure and traffic management. The platform uses a distributed architecture spread across global data centers, allowing for flexible scaling. Advanced load balancing distributes incoming requests efficiently, while extensive caching and Content Delivery Networks speed up content delivery. X implements data sharding to optimize database operations and utilizes cloud-based auto-scaling to adjust resources dynamically. These techniques, combined with robust monitoring and failover systems, enable X to maintain stability during high-traffic periods. However, like any complex system, X isn't immune to occasional disruptions during extreme events and may employ temporary feature limitations to preserve core functionality when necessary.  #tech #stem #techexpert #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oAaNWBGfECCIbuXReIAgIi9L2tt7pfYJidmjSa?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=UO45ZoeyDIW6sdGMqEbz2PMvMAg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oAaNWBGfECCIbuXReIAgIi9L2tt7pfYJidmjSa?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=UO45ZoeyDIW6sdGMqEbz2PMvMAg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oAaNWBGfECCIbuXReIAgIi9L2tt7pfYJidmjSa?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=UO45ZoeyDIW6sdGMqEbz2PMvMAg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Cupidon &amp; Milaa çš„ Feel It åˆ›ä½œçš„ Did you know you were helping train AI this way?  Are you training A.I. when using these? Also, I don't know about you, but I overthink these terribly. Okay, but here's how they work technically. But first, did you know the founder of Duolingo is also the founder of the tech behind these CAPTCHAs? Pretty crazy. User solves CAPTCHA. They're typically presented with two images or two words. One is known in the system or the control, and the other is unknown and needs labeling. That's where the help of you comes in by correctly solving the challenge. Your response to the unknown item is considered reliable, but it brings up a question If the other item is not known to the system, how does it know if you actually got it right? One way is through consensus verification. The same unknown item is shown to multiple users going through selecting the right image or text. <img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ iMiðŸ«§ çš„ Dominic x Brazil Declan åˆ›ä½œçš„ Dont miss out on these three prompts for job hunting ðŸ‘‡ 1ï¸âƒ£Resume review and alignment prompt: &quot;Please review my resume and the following job posting, then provide a detailed analysis: [Paste your resume here] [Paste the job posting here] Analyze the alignment between my resume and the job requirements. Finally, offer 2-3 overall tips to make my resume more compelling for this specific position.&quot; 2ï¸âƒ£Customized cover letter creation prompt: &quot;Please help me create a customized cover letter for the following job posting: [Paste the job posting here] Here's a brief summary of my relevant experience and skills: [Provide a 3-5 sentence overview of your background] Please write a cover letter that: Addresses the hiring manager (use 'Dear Hiring Manager' if no name is provided) Opens with a strong, attention-grabbing first paragraph Highlights 3-4 of my most relevant skills or experiences that match the job requirements Includes a specific example of a relevant achievement Demonstrates my knowledge of the company and why I'm interested in the position Closes with a call to action and my enthusiasm for the role The tone should be professional yet personable. <img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tommy Richman çš„ DEVIL IS A LIE åˆ›ä½œçš„ The last one has happened to so many people. Important to be aware!  Deleting a file doesn't actually erase it from your computer  (TRUE): When you &quot;delete&quot; a file normally, the operating system only removes the file's entry from the file system table. The actual data remains on the storage device until it's overwritten by new data. Strong passwords alone are enough to protect accounts (FALSE):  While strong passwords are important, they're not sufficient on their own. Multi-factor authentication and regular password changes add crucial extra layers of security. Emails from known contacts are always safe (FALSE): Hackers can compromise email accounts or spoof familiar addresses. Always verify unexpected requests or links, even from known contacts, to guard against phishing attempts. #tech #technology #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/f60178a116ce418487d01802dc1e2fca_1720636904?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=yy9l5%2BBCxGTdegOUBxiAfICjMCE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/f60178a116ce418487d01802dc1e2fca_1720636904?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=yy9l5%2BBCxGTdegOUBxiAfICjMCE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/f60178a116ce418487d01802dc1e2fca_1720636904?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=yy9l5%2BBCxGTdegOUBxiAfICjMCE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

Quantum computing is like a super-powered calculator that can solve complex problems much faster than current computers. But using Ai to help is alot of fun.  Prompt 1:  Create a simple, playable 2D survival game using React and SVG graphics. The game's goal is to achieve the highest score possible by surviving as long as you can on a 10x10 grid-based board. Players control a character that moves one cell at a time in four directions using arrow keys or on-screen buttons, aiming to avoid 3-5 AI-controlled opponents that move randomly every few seconds. Increase the player's score by collecting randomly spawning items and lasting longer. End the game when the player collides with an opponent, displaying the final score and offering a restart option. Use basic SVG shapes with different colors to represent the player (e.g., blue circle), opponents (e.g., red circles), and collectable items (e.g., gold squares). Include simple sound effects for movements, item collection, and game over. Gradually increase difficulty by speeding up AI movements and adding more opponents as the score increases. Implement this game logic in a single React component, focusing on creating an engaging gameplay loop with clear objectives and escalating challenges. Prompt 2:  Create a React-based pixel art creator component that allows users to draw, erase, and fill pixels on a customizable canvas. Include options for different canvas sizes (16x16, 32x32, 64x64) and a color palette with both preset and custom colors. Implement drawing functionality that supports both clicking individual pixels and click-and-drag for continuous drawing. Add undo and redo capabilities to allow users to correct mistakes easily. Include a fill tool that can color-connected areas of the same color. Provide an export feature that saves the artwork as a high-quality PNG file. Use shadcn/ui components for the user interface, including buttons, selects, and popovers. Utilize the lucide-react library for icons. Ensure the component is responsive and user-friendly, with a clear layout for tools and color selection. The color palette should have a way to add custom colors using a color picker. Make sure to handle mouse events properly for smooth drawing operations. <img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What is the difference between TCP and UDP?  Imagine you're sending a package to a friend. TCP is like using a delivery service that requires a signature and confirmation when the package arrives. It's slower but ensures your package gets there safely and in the correct order. UDP, on the other hand, is like tossing your package over the fence and hoping it lands where it should. It's faster because there's no waiting for confirmation, but some packages might get lost or arrive out of order. In computer networks, TCP is used when accuracy is crucial (like for emails or file transfers), while UDP is used when speed is more important and a few errors are acceptable (like for streaming video or online gaming). #tech #stem #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/0b9263744803418e8f9420f9c174d627_1719274892?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8yh1HVQB83FV7p%2BmtxkeuqRGEyA%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/0b9263744803418e8f9420f9c174d627_1719274892?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8yh1HVQB83FV7p%2BmtxkeuqRGEyA%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/0b9263744803418e8f9420f9c174d627_1719274892?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8yh1HVQB83FV7p%2BmtxkeuqRGEyA%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What was the first video game created?  Video games have a complex origin story that challenges the notion of a single &quot;first&quot; video game. While many people believe Pong (1972) was the first, earlier inventions laid crucial groundwork. The 1948 Cathode-Ray Tube Amusement Device, 1951's Nimrod computer, and 1952's OXO all contributed to video game development. However, William Higinbotham's &quot;Tennis for Two&quot; (1958) is often cited as the first true video game, as it was designed purely for entertainment and featured moving graphics on screen. Despite these earlier inventions, Pong became the first game to capture wide public attention, popularizing video games for a mass audience. The evolution of video games demonstrates how technological advancements and changing definitions have shaped our understanding of this medium over time. #tech #techexpert #education #stem #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/4e85ebf1a08d4ce289e0a684c0f8aeef_1719179185?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=xPdklS6z9OgEQoQxeO%2FEYcstjrM%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/4e85ebf1a08d4ce289e0a684c0f8aeef_1719179185?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=xPdklS6z9OgEQoQxeO%2FEYcstjrM%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/4e85ebf1a08d4ce289e0a684c0f8aeef_1719179185?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=xPdklS6z9OgEQoQxeO%2FEYcstjrM%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Will python and computer vision save me from my coffee addiction? I created a Python script that uses OpenCV, a computer vision library, to detect when I take a drink of coffee from my mug. The script captures video from my camera, analyzes each frame to detect my face, and focuses on the mouth region. It counts the number of white pixels in the mouth area, and if the count exceeds a certain threshold, it considers it as a drinking action. <img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What is the difference between machine learning and deep learning?  Machine learning and deep learning are both subsets of artificial intelligence, but they differ in their approach and complexity. Machine learning involves training algorithms to learn patterns and make predictions from data, without being explicitly programmed. It can be used for tasks like spam detection or recommending products. Deep learning, on the other hand, is a more advanced form of machine learning that uses neural networks with many layers to learn from vast amounts of data. This allows it to tackle more complex problems, such as image and speech recognition, by learning hierarchical representations of data. In essence, deep learning is a more powerful and autonomous version of machine learning, capable of handling more intricate tasks. #tech #machinelearning #coding #technology " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/050f644cb43847338fe631f9e45a2d9d_1718031142~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ocAC4ZMuAJjfIFXILiADNIQGOgfSzApEgReTkU.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=XuSh1GeVndVlqo0rGYk7RVxC7tQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/050f644cb43847338fe631f9e45a2d9d_1718031142~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ocAC4ZMuAJjfIFXILiADNIQGOgfSzApEgReTkU.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=XuSh1GeVndVlqo0rGYk7RVxC7tQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/050f644cb43847338fe631f9e45a2d9d_1718031142~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ocAC4ZMuAJjfIFXILiADNIQGOgfSzApEgReTkU.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=XuSh1GeVndVlqo0rGYk7RVxC7tQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What is Kubernetes?  Kubernetes is a tool that helps manage and organize applications running on multiple computers or servers. Think of it as a conductor in an orchestra, making sure all the musicians (applications) are playing together smoothly and efficiently. It allows you to easily deploy, scale, and manage your applications across a cluster of machines. This means you can run your applications reliably, handle more traffic, and update them without downtime. In simple terms, Kubernetes makes it easier to run and manage applications in a world where everything is becoming more distributed and complex. #tech #technology #techexplained #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/3d96c6d29cd64ef99f4dab6b63339a70_1717600389?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=YggTw2rTiqPjAWpWhlAXy2YSddk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/3d96c6d29cd64ef99f4dab6b63339a70_1717600389?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=YggTw2rTiqPjAWpWhlAXy2YSddk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/3d96c6d29cd64ef99f4dab6b63339a70_1717600389?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=YggTw2rTiqPjAWpWhlAXy2YSddk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What is TCP? Explained simply so you dont forget it ðŸ‘‡ TCP, which stands for Transmission Control Protocol, is a fundamental protocol used in computer networks to ensure reliable, ordered, and error-checked delivery of data between applications running on hosts communicating over an IP network. In simple terms, TCP is like a trustworthy postal service for the internet. When you send data using TCP, it breaks the data into smaller, numbered packages and sends them to the recipient. TCP ensures that all the packages arrive in the correct order and without any errors. If a package is lost or damaged along the way, TCP detects this and resends the package until it arrives intact. Once all the packages have been received, TCP reassembles them into the original data, making sure that the recipient gets exactly what was sent. This reliable, ordered delivery makes TCP essential for many applications, such as web browsing, email, and file transfers, where the integrity and completeness of the data are crucial. #tech #stem #technology #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/2011bda4e08d425ca0bfce4009e6d105_1717488117~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ocIA9m7ECCsAWQR23XQACFEBnkDH9XAHNfuxfJ.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=d3AM%2B9GOoV1QmurgNRqwBfgOxd0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/2011bda4e08d425ca0bfce4009e6d105_1717488117~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ocIA9m7ECCsAWQR23XQACFEBnkDH9XAHNfuxfJ.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=d3AM%2B9GOoV1QmurgNRqwBfgOxd0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/2011bda4e08d425ca0bfce4009e6d105_1717488117~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ocIA9m7ECCsAWQR23XQACFEBnkDH9XAHNfuxfJ.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=d3AM%2B9GOoV1QmurgNRqwBfgOxd0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What is the difference between a load balancer and a reverse proxy?  A load balancer and a reverse proxy serve different primary purposes, although they share some similarities. A load balancer focuses on distributing incoming network traffic across multiple backend servers to optimize resource usage, maximize throughput, and minimize response time. On the other hand, a reverse proxy acts as an intermediary between clients and servers, providing an additional layer of security, performing tasks such as SSL termination, caching, compression, and URL rewriting before forwarding client requests to the appropriate server. #stem #tech #technology #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/6719ea6dbab94aac8612307d6b029330_1717107935~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oYExwNQQEbDAWJtFPRCMCmfznAxBREAAIlNrfR.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=z2syO6CeK2aWdeMVj283%2BUh8X3k%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/6719ea6dbab94aac8612307d6b029330_1717107935~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oYExwNQQEbDAWJtFPRCMCmfznAxBREAAIlNrfR.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=z2syO6CeK2aWdeMVj283%2BUh8X3k%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/6719ea6dbab94aac8612307d6b029330_1717107935~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oYExwNQQEbDAWJtFPRCMCmfznAxBREAAIlNrfR.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=z2syO6CeK2aWdeMVj283%2BUh8X3k%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What is RAG in AI?  Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) is a technique that improves the output of large language models (LLMs) by allowing them to access and reference external knowledge sources before generating a response. LLMs are powerful AI models that can generate human-like text for various tasks, but they may sometimes produce irrelevant or outdated information. RAG enhances LLMs by enabling them to retrieve relevant information from a knowledge base, such as an organization's internal documents or a specific domain's authoritative sources. This retrieved information is then used to guide the LLM in generating more accurate, up-to-date, and context-appropriate responses. The importance of RAG lies in its ability to: 1. Improve the relevance and accuracy of LLM-powered chatbots and applications. 2. Provide a cost-effective way to adapt LLMs to specific domains or knowledge bases without retraining the entire model. 3. Address the limitations of static training data and make LLMs more reliable for real-world use cases. #stem #tech #ai #techexplained #techexpert " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/4e987b116f704b5d8dcfcc6c37a24699_1717025811~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oIZBEXqRAGI8hAAAevlIeLAvAFkpfIttGvXfLA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8TWhJAmGGc53HVeaySYMzhBic8A%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/4e987b116f704b5d8dcfcc6c37a24699_1717025811~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oIZBEXqRAGI8hAAAevlIeLAvAFkpfIttGvXfLA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8TWhJAmGGc53HVeaySYMzhBic8A%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/4e987b116f704b5d8dcfcc6c37a24699_1717025811~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oIZBEXqRAGI8hAAAevlIeLAvAFkpfIttGvXfLA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=8TWhJAmGGc53HVeaySYMzhBic8A%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ The main difference between an API (Application Programming Interface) and an SDK (Software Development Kit) lies in their scope and purpose. An API is a set of rules, protocols, and tools that allows different software applications to communicate and exchange data with each other. It defines how developers can request information or functionality from another application, specifying the types of requests and responses. In contrast, an SDK is a more comprehensive package that includes a collection of tools, libraries, documentation, code samples, and guides to help developers build applications for a specific platform or system. SDKs often include APIs as part of their toolkit, but they provide a broader set of resources to facilitate development within a particular ecosystem, enabling developers to get started more quickly and efficiently. #tech #techexplained #developer #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/11be4e90db1b40aa9592c88862aa0530_1716670166?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=Yz1QSD1w%2FxAhn%2BnnxWW1AqlUIGg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/11be4e90db1b40aa9592c88862aa0530_1716670166?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=Yz1QSD1w%2FxAhn%2BnnxWW1AqlUIGg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/11be4e90db1b40aa9592c88862aa0530_1716670166?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=Yz1QSD1w%2FxAhn%2BnnxWW1AqlUIGg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What is Kubernetes?!  Here are three key points to remember about Kubernetes: 1. Container orchestration: Kubernetes is a container orchestration platform that manages and coordinates containerized applications across a cluster of machines, ensuring they run efficiently and reliably. 2. Scalability and self-healing: Kubernetes allows you to easily scale applications up or down based on demand and automatically recovers from failures, such as restarting or replacing failed containers or nodes. 3. Infrastructure abstraction: Kubernetes abstracts away the complexities of the underlying infrastructure, allowing developers to focus on building and deploying applications without worrying about the specific details of the hardware or networking. #tech #techexplained #coding #stem #developer " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/eeb6175587704219ac170ddd9ce4034c_1716253642?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=cyOjjUIcUA23XObtogihLo3M1kw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/eeb6175587704219ac170ddd9ce4034c_1716253642?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=cyOjjUIcUA23XObtogihLo3M1kw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/eeb6175587704219ac170ddd9ce4034c_1716253642?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=cyOjjUIcUA23XObtogihLo3M1kw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What is Kubernetes? Kubernetes is an open-source container orchestration platform that automates the deployment, scaling, and management of containerized applications. Here's a simple explanation of how it works: 1. Containers: Applications are packaged into containers, which are lightweight and portable units that contain everything needed to run the application (code, libraries, dependencies, etc.). 2. Clusters: Kubernetes organizes containers into clusters, which are groups of machines (nodes) that work together to run applications. 3. Pods: Containers are grouped into pods, which are the smallest deployable units in Kubernetes. Pods can contain one or more containers that share the same resources and network. 4. Deployments: Kubernetes uses deployments to manage the lifecycle of pods, ensuring that the desired number of replicas are running and updating them when necessary. 5. Services: Kubernetes uses services to provide a stable network endpoint for accessing pods, allowing them to communicate with each other and with the outside world. 6. Scaling: Kubernetes can automatically scale the number of pods up or down based on resource usage or other metrics, ensuring that applications can handle variable workloads. In summary, Kubernetes provides a way to efficiently manage and scale containerized applications across a cluster of machines, making it easier to deploy, update, and maintain complex applications in a distributed environment. #tech #stem #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ooZBBvkxgTBSiOhE4GIoMQzAE7CIAPiUxS4tY?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=tx960SB0bFJN3qZ6yoGuKbTrFAo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ooZBBvkxgTBSiOhE4GIoMQzAE7CIAPiUxS4tY?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=tx960SB0bFJN3qZ6yoGuKbTrFAo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ooZBBvkxgTBSiOhE4GIoMQzAE7CIAPiUxS4tY?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=tx960SB0bFJN3qZ6yoGuKbTrFAo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What is the difference between a forward and reverse proxy?  Reverse Proxy: - Load balancing: Distributes traffic across multiple servers - Increased security: Acts as a single entry point, hiding backend servers - Caching: Improves performance by serving cached content - SSL termination: Handles SSL encryption, reducing load on backend servers - Real-world example: Netflix uses a combination of NGINX and Amazon Web Services (AWS) Elastic Load Balancer (ELB) as a reverse proxy to handle massive traffic and ensure smooth content delivery to its users worldwide. Forward Proxy: - Anonymity: Hides client IP address from the target server - Access control: Allows or blocks access to specific websites or content - Caching: Reduces bandwidth usage and improves performance for frequently accessed content - Content filtering: Blocks inappropriate or malicious content based on predefined rules - Real-world example: Many organizations, such as schools and businesses, use forward proxies like Squid or FortiGate to control and monitor internet access, block inappropriate content, and protect their network from external threats" fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/5473c879f7714bac97b59aebc3f56a81_1715791710?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=K5n2FfzV9T1KaGZGtMdSUIVXX2g%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/5473c879f7714bac97b59aebc3f56a81_1715791710?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=K5n2FfzV9T1KaGZGtMdSUIVXX2g%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/5473c879f7714bac97b59aebc3f56a81_1715791710?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=K5n2FfzV9T1KaGZGtMdSUIVXX2g%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Why do apps load the beginning of many videos instead of fully loading just one when you don't have internet service? Apps like TikTok and YouTube partially preload multiple videos instead of fully loading one for several reasons: 1. It allows users to quickly switch between videos, providing a smoother browsing experience. 2. It optimizes bandwidth usage, reducing data consumption for both the user and the platform. 3. It accommodates uncertainty about which video the user will watch entirely. 4. It manages device resources more efficiently by distributing memory and processing power across multiple videos. 5. It adapts to variable network conditions, prioritizing which videos to continue buffering. 6. It balances user experience and cost-effectiveness for the platform. #tech #stem #techexpert #techexplained  " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/55058df841a143908e7708574412458f_1715445425?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=5F5topJVEKl%2BklvrUQ%2B4RJAzuGk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/55058df841a143908e7708574412458f_1715445425?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=5F5topJVEKl%2BklvrUQ%2B4RJAzuGk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/55058df841a143908e7708574412458f_1715445425?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=5F5topJVEKl%2BklvrUQ%2B4RJAzuGk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Who invented Wifi? Hedy Lamarr was an Austrian-American actress and inventor who pioneered the technology that would one day form the basis for today's WiFi, GPS, and Bluetooth communication systems. While many people and organizations were involved, the person who contributed the most to the WiFi we know today is Vic Hayes. Many consider Hayes, who invented WiFi and call him â€œthe father of WiFi.â€ Wi-Fi 6, also known as 802.11ax, is the latest generation of Wi-Fi technology, succeeding Wi-Fi 5 (802.11ac).  2.4 GHz is better for longer-range and compatibility but faces more interference and offers slower speeds. 5 GHz provides faster speeds and less interference but has a shorter range and requires more modern devices. 6 GHz (Wi-Fi 6E) offers the highest speeds and least interference but is limited in terms of device compatibility and range. #tech #techexplained #stem #coding " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ogb89ZKIP2hjiAIiaBB6PQUPZBSO9skiEiw3E?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=L2MlDA7LdN6uqKFcRdTji06%2FQkE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ogb89ZKIP2hjiAIiaBB6PQUPZBSO9skiEiw3E?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=L2MlDA7LdN6uqKFcRdTji06%2FQkE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ogb89ZKIP2hjiAIiaBB6PQUPZBSO9skiEiw3E?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=L2MlDA7LdN6uqKFcRdTji06%2FQkE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What is a container in tech? But explained simplyâ€¦.  Here are  containers other than Docket (which we here about the most)  1. LXC (Linux Containers): LXC is a container runtime that provides a virtual environment with its own process and network space. It's one of the oldest container technologies and forms the foundation for many other container runtimes. 2. LXD: LXD is a container hypervisor that builds on top of LXC. It provides a more user-friendly interface and additional features like live migration and storage management. 3. containerd: containerd is a standalone container runtime that was originally part of the Docker project. It's a lightweight, portable container runtime that focuses on simplicity and robustness. 4. CRI-O: CRI-O is a container runtime that implements the Kubernetes Container Runtime Interface (CRI). It's designed to be lightweight and optimized for Kubernetes. 5. Podman: Podman is a daemonless container engine that's compatible with the Docker CLI. It allows users to run containers as regular users, without requiring root privileges. 6. Rkt (Rocket): Rkt is a container engine developed by CoreOS (now part of Red Hat). It's designed to be composable, secure, and compatible with the App Container (appc) specification. 7. Windows Containers: Windows Containers is Microsoft's container technology that allows running Windows applications in isolated environments on Windows servers. #tech #technology #coding #stem #education " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/96bd45e499f24d70b25f19001967fcd9_1714857260?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=h5ODfLZSLpNpb25OAis%2BFAfnpos%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/96bd45e499f24d70b25f19001967fcd9_1714857260?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=h5ODfLZSLpNpb25OAis%2BFAfnpos%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/96bd45e499f24d70b25f19001967fcd9_1714857260?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=h5ODfLZSLpNpb25OAis%2BFAfnpos%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What is a Websocket and how is it different than HTTPS? A websocket is a communication protocol that allows real-time, bi-directional data transfer between a client and a server over a single, persistent connection. It's like having a telephone conversation, where both parties can send messages to each other at any time, without the need for a request-response cycle like in the traditional HTTP model. WebSocket is efficient, reducing overhead by eliminating HTTP headers, and is ideal for applications requiring real-time updates, such as chat apps, live feeds, or multi-player games. The server can push data to the client as soon as it's available, without the client having to poll for updates. To establish a WebSocket connection, the client sends an HTTP request with an &quot;Upgrade&quot; header, and if the server supports WebSocket, the connection is upgraded. From then on, the client and server can send messages using the WebSocket API, simplifying the development of real-time applications.  #tech #techexpert #techexplained #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/b3ce90f6c250447b917997aec69b94ce_1714602496?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=INj6BBUkWhfU0fTK%2BHlZssEnpjc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/b3ce90f6c250447b917997aec69b94ce_1714602496?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=INj6BBUkWhfU0fTK%2BHlZssEnpjc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/b3ce90f6c250447b917997aec69b94ce_1714602496?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=INj6BBUkWhfU0fTK%2BHlZssEnpjc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Why do so many people use DuckDuckGo to stay private? How private is it ...really? DuckDuckGo prioritizes user privacy, therefore it's a popular alternative to data-tracking search giants. Your searches are anonymous because it doesn't track IP addresses, use cookies, or create profiles. DuckDuckGo prevents sites from seeing your search terms, therefore enhancing privacy. But it can't hide your use of the search engine from your ISP. DuckDuckGo's privacy commitment extends to its browser apps and extensions, which block trackers and minimize data collection, therefore providing a comprehensive privacy ecosystem.  But it can't protect you from malicious websites, therefore caution is still necessary.  DuckDuckGo's open-source approach allows independent privacy audits, therefore setting it apart. It empowers users to control their data in an era of diminishing online privacy. But complete anonymity requires additional tools beyond DuckDuckGo, therefore it should be part of a broader privacy strategy. DuckDuckGo is a big deal because its robust privacy features react to prevalent tracking practices. Therefore, it's a go-to choice for the privacy-conscious in a data-driven online world. #tech #technology #techexplainer #security #cybersecurity #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/086a3f3d05ec48ec9583cd3cda13c268_1714513114~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oAIXfRCm6MiyTFM27kBDaQAEJuBfAXOAtQAkEW.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=s0UhTMRiANtnTQlSBEbAzrRwuJ0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/086a3f3d05ec48ec9583cd3cda13c268_1714513114~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oAIXfRCm6MiyTFM27kBDaQAEJuBfAXOAtQAkEW.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=s0UhTMRiANtnTQlSBEbAzrRwuJ0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/086a3f3d05ec48ec9583cd3cda13c268_1714513114~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oAIXfRCm6MiyTFM27kBDaQAEJuBfAXOAtQAkEW.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=s0UhTMRiANtnTQlSBEbAzrRwuJ0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ 3 categories of machine learning you should understand ðŸ’¡ 1. Supervised learning: The algorithm learns from labeled historical input and output data to create a model that can make predictions. Common algorithms include neural networks, decision trees, linear regression, and support vector machines. Used for tasks like sales forecasting, fraud detection, and predicting equipment failure. 2. Unsupervised learning: The algorithm finds patterns in unlabeled data to group data points into clusters. Common algorithms include Hidden Markov models, k-means, hierarchical clustering, and Gaussian mixture models. Used for customer segmentation, inventory grouping, and identifying associations in data.  3. Reinforcement learning: The algorithm learns through interaction with its environment, receiving positive or negative rewards. Common algorithms include temporal difference, deep adversarial networks, and Q-learning. Used in applications like autonomous vehicles, traffic control, and robotics, but requires high computing power. #tech #techexpert #techexplained #coding #stem #machinelearning #ai " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/786bfac729b14297abc5eb523fe0fc08_1714352990~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/o07umzmOiVx3AiXAQAEEAog8gSAFBuBzCIyfIX.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=uUe3NHkfu9Q7yLpZw1qMho7BCWs%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/786bfac729b14297abc5eb523fe0fc08_1714352990~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/o07umzmOiVx3AiXAQAEEAog8gSAFBuBzCIyfIX.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=uUe3NHkfu9Q7yLpZw1qMho7BCWs%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/786bfac729b14297abc5eb523fe0fc08_1714352990~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/o07umzmOiVx3AiXAQAEEAog8gSAFBuBzCIyfIX.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=uUe3NHkfu9Q7yLpZw1qMho7BCWs%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What is a CRON job?  A cron job is a scheduled task that runs automatically at a specified time. It's commonly used to automate repetitive tasks without manual intervention. Real-world example: Generating daily sales reports 1. Write a script to:    - Retrieve sales data from the database    - Generate a formatted report    - Send the report via email    - Save a copy on the server 2. Set up a cron job to execute the script every morning at 6:00 AM:    - Edit the crontab file: `crontab -e`    - Add the line: `0 6 * * * /path/to/sales_report_script.py` 3. Save the crontab file and exit. The cron job will automatically run the script daily at 6:00 AM, generating and sending the sales report. Other common uses of cron jobs include: - Automating backups - Cleaning up log files - Sending notifications - Updating data feeds - Running maintenance tasks Cron jobs save time and effort by automating important, repetitive tasks in various domains. #tech #stem #technology #techexpert #programming " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/3ada5b294da345fb8c41ae830acea98c_1714173155?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2BNRDm4bKh9%2B8PFUlm%2BA4pMWo5m0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/3ada5b294da345fb8c41ae830acea98c_1714173155?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2BNRDm4bKh9%2B8PFUlm%2BA4pMWo5m0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/3ada5b294da345fb8c41ae830acea98c_1714173155?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2BNRDm4bKh9%2B8PFUlm%2BA4pMWo5m0%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What exactly is DNS? This is something you might hear often in a tech interview or at a company you're working for. You can think of DNS like a phone book before the Internet. Just as you would use a phone book. Okay. Well, maybe we don't use phone books anymore. Our parents would use phone books to look up someone's name and phone number in the phone book. DNS helps your computer find the right website based on its domain name. When you type in. I love dogs. I mean, I know dogs are better than cats, let's face it. But regardless, when you type it in, computer doesn't actually know where to find. I love dogs dot com. It needs to translate this domain into an IP address, which is a unique numerical label that is assigned to each device connected to the internet. That's where DNS comes in. Your computer will send a request to the DNS server asking for the IP address of Isle of Dogs dot com, and the DNS server will respond with the correct IP address allowing your computer to connect to Isle of Dogs dot com website. And this process happens every single time you type in a website you want to visit. Save for your next tech interview.  #tech #technology #stem #techexpert #techexplained #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/e25d50f942674259a9d634c9c203bb00_1713819660~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/okAGAfQiDBAmFAeEFmE0tUEAJCJIRIWQ7VR0AA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=ja%2BjBH6qx%2BXKniSpizFCfG5JOZk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/e25d50f942674259a9d634c9c203bb00_1713819660~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/okAGAfQiDBAmFAeEFmE0tUEAJCJIRIWQ7VR0AA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=ja%2BjBH6qx%2BXKniSpizFCfG5JOZk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/e25d50f942674259a9d634c9c203bb00_1713819660~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/okAGAfQiDBAmFAeEFmE0tUEAJCJIRIWQ7VR0AA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=ja%2BjBH6qx%2BXKniSpizFCfG5JOZk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ This is pretty cool ðŸ‘‡ SSL (Secure Sockets Layer) and its successor, TLS (Transport Layer Security), are cryptographic protocols that provide secure communication over the internet. They are essential for protecting sensitive information, such as passwords, credit card numbers, and personal data, as it travels between a client (like your web browser) and a server (like a website). Imagine you're sending a postcard with a sensitive message to a friend. Without a secure envelope, anyone who handles the postcard can read its contents. SSL/TLS acts like a secure envelope for your internet communication. When you visit a website with a URL that starts with &quot;https&quot; (like https://www.example.com), SSL/TLS creates an encrypted connection between your browser and the website's server. This process involves several steps: 1. The client sends a request to the server to establish a secure connection. 2. The server responds with its SSL/TLS certificate, which contains its public key and other information to verify its identity. 3. The client verifies the server's certificate and generates a unique session key. 4. The client encrypts the session key using the server's public key and sends it back to the server. 5. The server decrypts the session key using its private key, and from this point on, all communication between the client and server is encrypted using the session key. Now, any data you send or receive from the website, such as login credentials or financial information, is encrypted and unreadable to anyone who might intercept the communication. This helps protect your privacy and security online." fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/844746d4f73b40cf82995e6b5833c0ee_1713731907~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oAegiFtEEQBIQBJpXKfkSA9ARA31mDJsBAmTCA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=I%2FV7U3I78Pe4uLUAe2MBSRdmPGo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/844746d4f73b40cf82995e6b5833c0ee_1713731907~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oAegiFtEEQBIQBJpXKfkSA9ARA31mDJsBAmTCA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=I%2FV7U3I78Pe4uLUAe2MBSRdmPGo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/844746d4f73b40cf82995e6b5833c0ee_1713731907~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oAegiFtEEQBIQBJpXKfkSA9ARA31mDJsBAmTCA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=I%2FV7U3I78Pe4uLUAe2MBSRdmPGo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Danail Draganov çš„ Fresh Five åˆ›ä½œçš„ What is Apples Secure Enclave?  How secure is your iPhone, really? I mean, Apple talks about the secure enclave that they use, but what really is it? Let's go through a real world example so you can always remember what Apple's secure enclave is. First off, imagine you have a high security vault in a bank and it stores valuable items like gold, rare artifacts and confidential documents. Now you can think of the secure enclave like a heavily guarded room that has the vault within it. It has its own security systems, cameras and guards that operate independently from the rest of the bank's security. So when someone wants to access items in this room, they must go through a rigorous authentication process first. And this could be through providing biometric data such as your fingerprint. Once inside, all the secure operations happen within this vault, and the guards ensure that no unauthorized person is allowed to get in. Now, here's the really cool thing. Even if someone manages to breach the bank's main security system, they still won't be able to access items in the special room because it has its own unique key and security measures. This is a real world example as to how you can think of Apple's secure enclave system works to protect your sensitive information, like your passwords, biometric information on your iPhone or iPad. #apple #tech #techtok #techexpert #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMweQX7RQQRIAeiD3F8feClAGIykYMkxFDGNEr~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oQf1A7GAXz5sEoiu4priQCpBBDAQEIIiA8EAAg.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=aLSk%2F%2BQ5P2EAJHOjx6I6N2QcFFk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMweQX7RQQRIAeiD3F8feClAGIykYMkxFDGNEr~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oQf1A7GAXz5sEoiu4priQCpBBDAQEIIiA8EAAg.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=aLSk%2F%2BQ5P2EAJHOjx6I6N2QcFFk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMweQX7RQQRIAeiD3F8feClAGIykYMkxFDGNEr~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oQf1A7GAXz5sEoiu4priQCpBBDAQEIIiA8EAAg.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=aLSk%2F%2BQ5P2EAJHOjx6I6N2QcFFk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Fully generated AI videos using 1 imageðŸ¤¯ Microsoft just shared about their new AI framework called VASA-1. Here is what they had to say about it: We introduce VASA, a framework for generating lifelike talking faces of virtual charactors with appealing visual affective skills (VAS), given a single static image and a speech audio clip. Our premiere model, VASA-1, is capable of not only producing lip movements that are exquisitely synchronized with the audio, but also capturing a large spectrum of facial nuances and natural head motions that contribute to the perception of authenticity and liveliness. The core innovations include a holistic facial dynamics and head movement generation model that works in a face latent space, and the development of such an expressive and disentangled face latent space using videos. Through extensive experiments including evaluation on a set of new metrics, we show that our method significantly outperforms previous methods along various dimensions comprehensively. Our method not only delivers high video quality with realistic facial and head dynamics but also supports the online generation of 512x512 videos at up to 40 FPS with negligible starting latency.
