<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ How does Spotify recommendations algorithm work?  Spotify employs a complex system of machine learning algorithms and data analysis to provide personalized music recommendations to its users. Here's an overview of the key components and techniques used in Spotify's recommendation system: 1. Collaborative Filtering:    - Spotify uses collaborative filtering to identify patterns and similarities in user behavior and preferences.    - It analyzes user-item interactions, such as liked songs, playlists, and listening history, to find users with similar tastes.    - By identifying similar users, Spotify can recommend songs that those users have enjoyed but the current user hasn't discovered yet. 2. Content-Based Filtering:    - Spotify also employs content-based filtering, which focuses on the characteristics and features of the songs themselves.    - It analyzes various audio features like tempo, key, loudness, danceability, and more to understand the musical attributes of each track.    - By comparing the audio features of songs, Spotify can recommend tracks with similar characteristics to the ones a user has enjoyed. 3. Natural Language Processing (NLP):    - Spotify uses NLP techniques to process and understand user-generated text data, such as playlist titles, descriptions, and user reviews.    - By analyzing the semantic meaning and context of the text, Spotify can extract insights about the genre, mood, or theme of the music.    - This information is used to enhance the recommendation process by considering the contextual aspects of the music. 4. Deep Learning and Neural Networks:    - Spotify employs deep learning techniques, particularly neural networks, to learn complex patterns and representations from the vast amount of user and music data.    - Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) are used to process audio data and capture temporal dependencies in music.    - These deep learning models enable Spotify to generate more nuanced and contextually relevant recommendations. 5. Ensemble Methods:    - Spotify combines multiple recommendation algorithms and models to generate more accurate and diverse recommendations.    - Ensemble methods, such as weighted averaging or ranking aggregation, are used to combine the outputs of different models.    - By leveraging the strengths of various algorithms, Spotify can provide more robust and personalized recommendations. #tech #techexplained #technology #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oEUQYBuIRhSHEkAZ0RIS1AipGvQEE0gy5iB7B~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oEARDEQYI1mAuqEhQCjA3JFAKEIfSBfasmAuUN.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=y2W%2FKYOuvAVzbbyX68DsRDqQmEI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oEUQYBuIRhSHEkAZ0RIS1AipGvQEE0gy5iB7B~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oEARDEQYI1mAuqEhQCjA3JFAKEIfSBfasmAuUN.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=y2W%2FKYOuvAVzbbyX68DsRDqQmEI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oEUQYBuIRhSHEkAZ0RIS1AipGvQEE0gy5iB7B~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oEARDEQYI1mAuqEhQCjA3JFAKEIfSBfasmAuUN.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=y2W%2FKYOuvAVzbbyX68DsRDqQmEI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Does using Tor Browser make you completely anonymous online?  It's a myth that most people think using Tor browser will make you totally anonymous online, when in reality there are a lot of exceptions to this. If you're not familiar with Tor browser, it is considered to be the most private browser out there to keep you anonymous when you're going online. But here's where it gets interesting. There are a few exceptions to stay anonymous when using Tor. Let's start with the obvious one. If you are logged in to your personal accounts on Tor, your identity can still be tied to your browsing session. Now here's another way that Tor might not be as secure as you think. Obviously, what computer you are using Tor on. If this computer is infected with malware or Keyloggers, your actions can still be monitor rendering tor to become useless. Now, many assume that Tor completely protects your identity, which makes your guard go down. Now, while Tor is a really great privacy tool, it is definitely not perfect, and it's very important to be aware of that. For more tech tips.  #tech #techtips #stem #technology " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oQTn3uUtBIoSDNz4AUiBkrId5AfTzAgEiLojCB?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=btdI%2BLZanS%2BXpBPp8S8DcsWoxMI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oQTn3uUtBIoSDNz4AUiBkrId5AfTzAgEiLojCB?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=btdI%2BLZanS%2BXpBPp8S8DcsWoxMI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oQTn3uUtBIoSDNz4AUiBkrId5AfTzAgEiLojCB?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=btdI%2BLZanS%2BXpBPp8S8DcsWoxMI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Have you ever wondered how does the Internet work?  I mean, like actually work? That's a pretty big question, but we're going to answer it. Let's start with the basics. Let's start with computers and devices. Of course, each computer and device has its own IP address, which is like a home address. But for the Internet and these devices are connected to the Internet through various ways. Then we have our ISP, or better known as Internet service providers. And all you need to know about this is these are the companies that give you access to the Internet. Why you pay them all the money, and it's your ISP that gives your device its IP address. So when you go to a website, your device sends a request over the Internet, and this request is broken down into small packets of data, each tagged with the IP address of your device. And these packets travel through various routers and switches which are in charge of directing the traffic efficiently. And eventually these packets reach the server hosting the website you want to visit. Then they need to turn around. This is the return journey. So the packets then after they've gone in the data for the website you want to visit, for example, make their way back to your device and they might follow a different path for this. <img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Come study machine learning with me A decision tree is like a flowchart that helps in making decisions based on yes/no questions. Imagine you're trying to decide what to wear today, and you have a decision tree to help you out. The tree starts at the root (the top) with a question about the weather.  - If it's raining (yes), the tree might tell you to wear a raincoat.  - If it's not raining (no), it asks another question, maybe about whether it's cold or not. Each time you answer a question, you follow the path down the tree that matches your answer, leading to new questions or to the end of the tree, where it tells you what to do (like wearing shorts if it's sunny and warm). In more technical terms, a decision tree is used in data science to help predict an outcome based on past data. It asks a series of true/false questions about the data (like is it raining, is it cold), and each question helps it get closer to predicting the outcome (like predicting if you should wear a coat or not). The decision tree makes these predictions by learning from examples (past data) and figuring out which questions are the best to ask and in what order. However, if the tree asks too many specific questions, it might get too focused on the examples it learned from and not be good at making predictions about new situations. So, sometimes it's necessary to simplify the tree to make it more useful for predicting new things. #tech #techexpert #futuretech " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/osVfjFxgARCRDDnfIlPBl2I0XwEE7lzJQBBuEr?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=0%2BnoccBYCZU8zVKzPy%2Bv9m5xGXg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/osVfjFxgARCRDDnfIlPBl2I0XwEE7lzJQBBuEr?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=0%2BnoccBYCZU8zVKzPy%2Bv9m5xGXg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/osVfjFxgARCRDDnfIlPBl2I0XwEE7lzJQBBuEr?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=0%2BnoccBYCZU8zVKzPy%2Bv9m5xGXg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ How can you tell if public Wi-Fi is safe?  When using public Wi-Fi, ensure it's secure to protect your data. Here's how: Seek Encryption: Opt for networks with WPA2 or WPA3 encryption, indicated by a required connection password. Verify the Network: Ensure you're connecting to an official network. Confirm the network name with an employee if unsure. Use a VPN: A Virtual Private Network encrypts your data, safeguarding your online activities from others on the network. Look for HTTPS: Websites starting with &quot;https://&quot; are encrypted, offering more security for your data. Enable Firewall: Activate your device's firewall to monitor and protect against unauthorized access. Disable File Sharing: Turn off file sharing to prevent access to your files by others on the network. <img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ How ChatGPT work technically?  Large Language Models (LLMs) like GPT are sophisticated systems designed to process and generate language, comprised of several key components: Training Data: The extensive collection of text (books, articles, websites) from which the model learns language patterns, styles, and context. Tokenization: Breaking down text into smaller pieces (tokens) for the model to process. Itâ€™s like preparing ingredients for cooking. Embeddings: Converting tokens into numerical values to help the model understand word meanings and relationships. Think of it as giving each word a unique numerical fingerprint. Transformer Architecture: The core technology that allows the model to understand context and generate text. It includes: Attention Mechanism: Helps the model focus on relevant parts of the text to produce coherent and context-aware responses. Pre-training and Fine-tuning: Pre-training: The broad learning phase where the model learns from its large dataset. Fine-tuning: Adjusting the model for specific tasks by training it on more targeted data. Output Layer: The component that translates the model's processed information back into human-readable text, whether it's answering questions, completing prompts, or creating content. Decoding Strategies: Techniques the model uses to select the most appropriate words for generating coherent and relevant text. #tech #education #stem #ai #artificialintelligence #chatgpt " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oA9A4AiTmVBCI6otD7ALiOqgfzkBryICYxETIt~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ogBUkxJEAdRbAQmIeCFlAxHDQoJQABkMfm6Eop.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=5FkzehNgE3DRMclmI8sBpqoTcyY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oA9A4AiTmVBCI6otD7ALiOqgfzkBryICYxETIt~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ogBUkxJEAdRbAQmIeCFlAxHDQoJQABkMfm6Eop.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=5FkzehNgE3DRMclmI8sBpqoTcyY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oA9A4AiTmVBCI6otD7ALiOqgfzkBryICYxETIt~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ogBUkxJEAdRbAQmIeCFlAxHDQoJQABkMfm6Eop.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=5FkzehNgE3DRMclmI8sBpqoTcyY%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Can cell phones cause explosions at gas stations? The belief that cell phones can cause explosions at gas stations is a myth. Scientific evidence and research have shown that cell phones do not produce enough energy to ignite gasoline vapors. Regulatory bodies and safety organizations, including the FCC and the Petroleum Equipment Institute, confirm there's no evidence linking cell phones to gas station fires or explosions. The real risk comes from static electricity discharge, not mobile phones. While safety warnings exist, they're precautionary measures against potential risks and distractions, not based on incidents caused by cell phones. #tech #technology " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ooer6RDveXhuIAIpe0YLfRyGEXSWkQGJ8vkACF?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=0JD5%2FoWk%2FWtgkaJkFch%2FhzX09Uo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ooer6RDveXhuIAIpe0YLfRyGEXSWkQGJ8vkACF?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=0JD5%2FoWk%2FWtgkaJkFch%2FhzX09Uo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ooer6RDveXhuIAIpe0YLfRyGEXSWkQGJ8vkACF?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=0JD5%2FoWk%2FWtgkaJkFch%2FhzX09Uo%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Are you team dark mode or light mode?! Benefits of Light Mode on the Eyes: âž¡ï¸Enhanced Readability in Well-Lit Conditions: Bright backgrounds with dark text (classic light mode) can offer better readability in brightly lit environments or during the day. âž¡ï¸Reduced Pupil Dilation: Light mode causes the pupils to constrict, which can result in sharper vision and potentially less strain when focusing on detailed tasks. âž¡ï¸Optimal for Detailed Work: High contrast of dark text on a light background is generally preferred for tasks requiring focus and attention to detail. Benefits of Dark Mode on the Eyes: âž¡ï¸Reduced Glare in Low-Light Conditions: Dark mode can decrease screen glare when using devices in darker environments, leading to less eye strain. âž¡ï¸Lower Blue Light Exposure: May reduce exposure to blue light, which is linked to sleep disturbances, making it beneficial before bedtime. âž¡ï¸Potential Relief for Light Sensitivity: Individuals with photophobia or light sensitivity might find dark mode more comfortable for extended screen use. Each mode offers distinct advantages depending on the user's environment, time of day, and specific visual needs. Switching between modes based on these factors can help maximize comfort and minimize eye strain. #tech #technology #techexplained #techexpert " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/1ea252c6b1dd49e0a69860a849f0d7ae_1709326795?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=lVoX1gv%2FOxqehUmq9%2Bs7nCDPKBA%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/1ea252c6b1dd49e0a69860a849f0d7ae_1709326795?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=lVoX1gv%2FOxqehUmq9%2Bs7nCDPKBA%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/1ea252c6b1dd49e0a69860a849f0d7ae_1709326795?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=lVoX1gv%2FOxqehUmq9%2Bs7nCDPKBA%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ How does live straming actually work?!  Real-time live streaming on platforms like YouTube involves capturing video and audio content, compressing and encoding it in a streamable format almost instantaneously, and then transmitting it over the internet to viewers in near real-time.  This process employs protocols like Real-Time Messaging Protocol (RTMP) or HTTP Live Streaming (HLS) to manage the delivery of live content.  Adaptive bitrate streaming (ABS) is also crucial, adjusting the stream quality in real-time based on each viewer's network speed and device performance to minimize buffering and ensure a smooth viewing experience.  Behind the scenes, distributed content delivery networks (CDNs) play a vital role in reducing latency by caching streams on edge servers closer to the audience, enhancing the scalability and reliability of live streaming services. #tech #techexpert #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/e358ed1d90a24f3584d6c1951df582d7_1708546249?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=gh7m%2B657b9ppiKikOdDUDFVxMPk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/e358ed1d90a24f3584d6c1951df582d7_1708546249?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=gh7m%2B657b9ppiKikOdDUDFVxMPk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/e358ed1d90a24f3584d6c1951df582d7_1708546249?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=gh7m%2B657b9ppiKikOdDUDFVxMPk%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Why is WhatsApp considered the most secure messaging app?  It's used by billions of people worldwide, raising the question of how it maintains the security of everyone's messages. WhatsApp employs several methods to ensure user security. While it is regarded by some as the most secure messaging app, how does it achieve this? Moreover, how feasible is it to intercept these messages? When you send a message to your friend via WhatsApp, it utilizes end-to-end encryption. This means your messages are encrypted with a unique lock on your device before they are even sent over the internet and can only be decrypted by the recipient's device. But how does the recipient's device know how to decrypt the message?  This begins when two users start a conversation; their devices perform a digital handshake, securely exchanging cryptographic keys through a process known as the Diffie-Hellman key exchange. What's important to understand is that this process ensures both parties have the necessary keys to encrypt and decrypt messages, but these keys are never exposed to WhatsApp or any other third party. So, how difficult would it be to intercept WhatsApp messages? From a theoretical standpoint, with unlimited resources, time, and the future development of powerful quantum computers, it might be possible to crack the encryption. However, in practical terms, with current technology, it is virtually impossible to intercept and decrypt messages without access to the private keys, which are securely stored on the devices of the communicating parties. #tech #techexplained #techexpert #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/56ac9dfdc302431d967bab8a4c630856_1707956679?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=6mhkyCO%2BOKxQvDMKP209%2FR14jW8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/56ac9dfdc302431d967bab8a4c630856_1707956679?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=6mhkyCO%2BOKxQvDMKP209%2FR14jW8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/56ac9dfdc302431d967bab8a4c630856_1707956679?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=6mhkyCO%2BOKxQvDMKP209%2FR14jW8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ AI/ML concepts/tools I learned about in my first class ðŸ‘‡ Anaconda Navigator and Jupyter Notebook are popular tools among data scientists, developers, and researchers for managing projects and performing data analysis. ðŸ¤–Anaconda Navigator Anaconda Navigator is a graphical user interface (GUI) included with the Anaconda distribution, which is a popular Python distribution used for scientific computing. Navigator provides a user-friendly way to launch applications included with Anaconda without needing to use command-line instructions. It's designed to make it easier to manage your Anaconda environment and the various packages, libraries, and tools that come with it. Managing Environments: You can create, export, list, remove, and update environments that have different versions of Python and/or packages installed. Launching Applications: Navigator allows you to launch applications included with Anaconda, such as Jupyter Notebooks, JupyterLab, Spyder (an IDE for Python), RStudio (if you have R installed), and others, with just a click. Managing Packages: It provides a graphical interface for installing, updating, and uninstalling Python packages. This can be especially helpful for those who prefer not to use the command line. ðŸ’»Jupyter Notebook Jupyter Notebook is an open-source web application that allows you to create and share documents that contain live code, equations, visualizations, and narrative text. It's part of the Project Jupyter and is widely used for data cleaning and transformation, numerical simulation, statistical modeling, data visualization, machine learning, and much more.  Interactive Computing: Jupyter Notebooks provide an interactive environment where you can execute code in a step-by-step manner and see immediate results. This is great for exploratory analysis and experimenting with code. #tech #ai #artificialintelligence #coding #python " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/owqvw0AggPYAXIetfJJRcueAWOfKMiEuQCif4q?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=TVmwhnwMxAVzT92HJsnHd15zlzc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/owqvw0AggPYAXIetfJJRcueAWOfKMiEuQCif4q?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=TVmwhnwMxAVzT92HJsnHd15zlzc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/owqvw0AggPYAXIetfJJRcueAWOfKMiEuQCif4q?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=TVmwhnwMxAVzT92HJsnHd15zlzc%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Netflix uses Chaos Engineering, specifically through their tool known as Chaos Monkey, to enhance the resilience and reliability of their systems, ensuring a seamless streaming experience for users worldwide. Chaos Engineering involves injecting controlled chaos into systems to identify and address potential weaknesses. Chaos Monkey plays a central role in this process by randomly terminating instances in Netflix's production environment. This simulation of real-world failures allows engineers to observe how systems respond and to improve fault tolerance. By embracing the unpredictability of failures, Netflix engineers are able to strengthen their architecture, ensuring that it can handle disruptions gracefully and maintain uninterrupted service for users. This approach to system design not only improves reliability but also prepares the infrastructure to withstand and quickly recover from unforeseen challenges. #ai #stem #tech #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/o4gjglEXfABYBeDWEmnFHtIQXFRnYxlVPJEEBU?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=AhEMQliAxOBPb%2BB%2FtcFVzvkDkU8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/o4gjglEXfABYBeDWEmnFHtIQXFRnYxlVPJEEBU?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=AhEMQliAxOBPb%2BB%2FtcFVzvkDkU8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/o4gjglEXfABYBeDWEmnFHtIQXFRnYxlVPJEEBU?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=AhEMQliAxOBPb%2BB%2FtcFVzvkDkU8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Cat Janice çš„ Dance You Outta My Head åˆ›ä½œçš„ Resources and tios I used to self study AI/ML ðŸ‘‡ Ironically, use AI! <img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Zen music çš„ Content Music Background (Live) åˆ›ä½œçš„ How does the blockchain actually work?  Implementing blockchain in the supply chain, like tracing coffee beans from farm to shop, involves assigning a unique digital identity to each batch, recording every transaction as a block on the blockchain, and linking these blocks to form a chain. This process is secured through decentralized verification by network participants, ensuring that each transaction is valid and making the ledger immutable. The blockchain can be public for transparency or permissioned for privacy, allowing stakeholders to trace the product's journey securely and efficiently. Additionally, smart contracts automate transactions, such as payments, once certain conditions are met, reducing the need for intermediaries and streamlining the supply chain process. This system enhances trust among consumers and operational efficiencies for businesses. #tech #stem #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oIvBo0ZVJKQ3EUSBxFDZrCdBFijAcBHiIEzNF~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oABvc3QZA0AdcqOTBLERAQHD6Izii64AUBEFi.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=O4shbxww5BeWGMOh8J4JlLEd6%2FI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oIvBo0ZVJKQ3EUSBxFDZrCdBFijAcBHiIEzNF~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oABvc3QZA0AdcqOTBLERAQHD6Izii64AUBEFi.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=O4shbxww5BeWGMOh8J4JlLEd6%2FI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oIvBo0ZVJKQ3EUSBxFDZrCdBFijAcBHiIEzNF~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oABvc3QZA0AdcqOTBLERAQHD6Izii64AUBEFi.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=O4shbxww5BeWGMOh8J4JlLEd6%2FI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What exactly is Big-O notation?!  Big-O notation might sound a bit technical, but it's really just a way to describe how fast a computer algorithm works, kind of like a speedometer for code. Let's use the example of looking for a name in a phone book. If the phone book isn't sorted and you have to go through each name one by one, this is like a linear search, or O(n). It's straightforward but gets slower as the phone book gets bigger. Now, if the phone book is sorted, you can use a smarter method called binary search, or O(log n), where you keep cutting the list in half. It's like playing a clever game of 'hot and cold' and gets you to the right name much faster, especially in a really big phone book. And finally, if you just need to pick out the very first name in the phone book, thatâ€™s a constant time operation, or O(1) - super quick and the size of the phone book doesnâ€™t matter. Big-O notation is a handy way to talk about these different scenarios and understand why some methods are quicker than others, especially when you're dealing with a lot of data. #tech #bigo #technology #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ca81ee9d3d784584a39ef8bd8cd383db_1706659464?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2FpZ5TCfj3yIazWfn8hi%2B2Tfq07Q%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ca81ee9d3d784584a39ef8bd8cd383db_1706659464?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2FpZ5TCfj3yIazWfn8hi%2B2Tfq07Q%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/ca81ee9d3d784584a39ef8bd8cd383db_1706659464?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2FpZ5TCfj3yIazWfn8hi%2B2Tfq07Q%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ How does ChatGPT technically work? When receiving user input, it undergoes preprocessing and tokenization to convert text into a machine-readable format. These tokens are then embedded into vectors and processed by the transformer neural network, which uses mechanisms to understand contextual nuances.  With ChatGPT, a large aspect of its functionality is Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback (RLHF), where it's fine-tuned with human input to ensure the responses are not only contextually appropriate but also aligned with being helpful, truthful, and harmless. This helps ChatGPT to provide responses that are coherent and contextually relevant.  #tech #technology #techexplainers #techtok #ai #artificial_intelligence " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/owIIWFLatIGf7hCAGeCgeiIhLrQSjAuCSqBwBC~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oowrRYsilIJAEABlBCtFAFIEQHDAtMA5JQfeBC.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2By5X8bPvyMiW%2BrKNbvV49NbX4y8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/owIIWFLatIGf7hCAGeCgeiIhLrQSjAuCSqBwBC~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oowrRYsilIJAEABlBCtFAFIEQHDAtMA5JQfeBC.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2By5X8bPvyMiW%2BrKNbvV49NbX4y8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/owIIWFLatIGf7hCAGeCgeiIhLrQSjAuCSqBwBC~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oowrRYsilIJAEABlBCtFAFIEQHDAtMA5JQfeBC.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2By5X8bPvyMiW%2BrKNbvV49NbX4y8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Do you really nees to switch your phone to airplane mode during a flight?!  When you activate airplane mode, or flight mode, on your phone, it turns off wireless and cellular signals to prevent interference with aircraft systems, as recommended by the FAA. In this mode, you can still manually enable Wi-Fi and Bluetooth if your plane and airline allow it. If you don't use airplane mode, your phone's radio transmissions could interfere with the plane's communication and navigation, especially during critical phases like reduced-visibility landings. While you could technically make cellular calls at lower altitudes, the FCC prohibits this in the U.S. when airborne. Regulations vary internationally, with the EU recently approving 5G use on planes, differing from U.S. restrictions due to variations in technology and safety considerations. #technology #tech " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oIACriLhDSjdIHaIL0Ad1IQGjgTSYR6CecefSg?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=4jD%2B5ICD8vQRPWPARE5CkTNGk%2Fg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oIACriLhDSjdIHaIL0Ad1IQGjgTSYR6CecefSg?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=4jD%2B5ICD8vQRPWPARE5CkTNGk%2Fg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oIACriLhDSjdIHaIL0Ad1IQGjgTSYR6CecefSg?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=4jD%2B5ICD8vQRPWPARE5CkTNGk%2Fg%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Is your phone actually listening to you?  Here is how you can block third party cookies.  On your computer, open Chrome. Select an option: -Allow third-party cookies. -Block third-party cookies in -Incognito mode. Block third-party cookies. If you block third-party cookies, all third-party cookies from other sites are blocked unless the site is allowed on your exceptions list. When you search for something on Google, the information is often tracked using cookies and shared across various advertising networks, including those used by social media platforms. This shared data allows social media sites to display ads relevant to your recent searches, utilizing sophisticated algorithms for targeted advertising. To help prevent this, you can use privacy-focused browsers like Firefox or Brave, which offer enhanced privacy settings to limit tracking. Adjusting your browser settings to block third-party cookies, regularly clearing your cookies, and using incognito or private browsing modes can also reduce tracking. Additionally, installing ad-blocking and anti-tracking extensions like uBlock Origin or Privacy Badger can help. Opting out of targeted advertising through tools provided by the Digital Advertising Alliance or the Network Advertising Initiative can further limit ad targeting based on your online activity. <img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Why are keyboards not in alphabetical order?  There is another theory than the video that suggests the QWERTY keyboard layout was influenced by this The theory suggests that the QWERTY keyboard was influenced by Morse code. While the theory about reducing typewriter jams is widely accepted, some historians have proposed that Morse code played a role in shaping the arrangement of keys. According to this theory, Christopher Sholes, the inventor of the typewriter and the QWERTY layout, may have been inspired by Morse code when designing the keyboard. Morse code is a system of representing letters and numbers using combinations of dots and dashes, and it was well-known during the time when the typewriter was being developed. Some argue that Sholes may have organized the keys to make typing Morse code more efficient, as early telegraph operators were required to have a good understanding of Morse code. #tech #techexplained #techexpert " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMWmBf7eDB2lFqOEilExccErpBJIPcWQyoRGYA~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/o4IIt1BdEiANIxB0vAiEAxCAg5uOfIGlyLrCo3.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=w2hSS%2BTkRQneAthgIWJ4y069kHA%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMWmBf7eDB2lFqOEilExccErpBJIPcWQyoRGYA~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/o4IIt1BdEiANIxB0vAiEAxCAg5uOfIGlyLrCo3.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=w2hSS%2BTkRQneAthgIWJ4y069kHA%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oMWmBf7eDB2lFqOEilExccErpBJIPcWQyoRGYA~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/o4IIt1BdEiANIxB0vAiEAxCAg5uOfIGlyLrCo3.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=w2hSS%2BTkRQneAthgIWJ4y069kHA%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What is DNS?  DNS stands for Domain Name System. It's like the phone book of the internet. Just like you look up a person's name in a phone book to find their phone number, your computer uses DNS to look up a website's name to find its internet address (which is a number). When you type a website name like &quot;google.com&quot; into your browser, DNS is what helps your computer find the right server on the internet where that website is located, using the website's IP address. This process happens very quickly, allowing you to access websites easily just by knowing their names. #tech #techtok #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/de5462e60cef4a4fbaeca184e71cceb3_1704845097?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=fbv%2By5r%2B5%2F1Djtt3AWfPCUn9MlQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/de5462e60cef4a4fbaeca184e71cceb3_1704845097?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=fbv%2By5r%2B5%2F1Djtt3AWfPCUn9MlQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/de5462e60cef4a4fbaeca184e71cceb3_1704845097?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=fbv%2By5r%2B5%2F1Djtt3AWfPCUn9MlQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ How does your cell phone magically connects you to anyone, anywhere? 1. Voice to Data: Your microphone captures your voice vibrations as analog signals. A microchip inside your phone converts these signals into a digital stream of numbers (think Morse code for sound!). Coding algorithms (codecs) like G.729 compress this data by removing redundancies, making it smaller for travel. 2. Data Takes Flight: The data transforms into a radio wave using modulation. Think of riding a sound wave (voice data) on top of a radio wave (carrier). Your phone's internal antenna blasts this modulated wave into the air. 3. The Cellular Symphony: Nearby cell towers receive the wave, extract the data (demodulation), and send it to the cellular network.  Smart computers called switching centers figure out where to send the data based on the recipient's number and network. The data jumps through the network like a digital hopscotch game, hopping between switching centers until it reaches the destination base station. 4. Data Back to Voice: The destination base station sends the data back out as a radio wave to the recipient's phone. Their phone's antenna receives the wave, extracts the data, and converts it back into electrical signals. Finally, a digital-to-analog converter transforms these signals back into sound waves, recreating your voice in their ear!" fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/56eab529e38a47c6b4b7887e0187e129_1704666695?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=rW9mFZHhLRp0gMNGGs4zyOk4d%2BU%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/56eab529e38a47c6b4b7887e0187e129_1704666695?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=rW9mFZHhLRp0gMNGGs4zyOk4d%2BU%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/56eab529e38a47c6b4b7887e0187e129_1704666695?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=rW9mFZHhLRp0gMNGGs4zyOk4d%2BU%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">
https://www.tiktok.com/@tiffintech/video/7321093966168952069
<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Youâ€™re not really deleting those files.  When you delete a file on your Mac, it doesn't vanish into thin air! It hangs out on your hard drive like a ghost hiding in the library stacks. Even though you can't see it on your desktop anymore, the actual file data is still there, chilling in unused space until something new writes over it.  This is why you can sometimes recover accidentally deleted files. Think of it like this: deleting a file is like removing the bookmark from your favorite book in the library catalog. The book itself is still on the shelf, just waiting for someone else to discover it. But if you really want that book gone for good, you need to shred it into tiny pieces, not just remove the bookmark.  #tech #techexpert #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oA1ZRbnTlEJ8E7B9wBmiYWeiIHBAQCAl4QfCDw?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=dsID0uV3FxPT48TZsoL9Cb6Sq5k%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oA1ZRbnTlEJ8E7B9wBmiYWeiIHBAQCAl4QfCDw?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=dsID0uV3FxPT48TZsoL9Cb6Sq5k%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oA1ZRbnTlEJ8E7B9wBmiYWeiIHBAQCAl4QfCDw?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=dsID0uV3FxPT48TZsoL9Cb6Sq5k%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What happens when you type a url into the browser?  1. URL Parsing and DNS Lookup: The browser interprets the URL and uses DNS to convert the domain name into an IP address. 2. Connection Establishment: The browser establishes a TCP connection to the server (using TLS for HTTPS). 3. HTTP Request and Response: The browser sends an HTTP request to the server. The server processes this request and sends back a response. 4. Rendering the Web Page: The browser renders the page from the received HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. 5. JavaScript Execution: JavaScript runs, potentially modifying the page and making additional requests. 6. Connection Management: The browser manages the connection, keeping it open for further requests or closing it as needed. #tech #techeducation #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/55a6d9f82a244de19d74a672cf522ecc_1704471097?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=qf0mR5MPHhk4RpamMO2GV4BtFOU%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/55a6d9f82a244de19d74a672cf522ecc_1704471097?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=qf0mR5MPHhk4RpamMO2GV4BtFOU%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/55a6d9f82a244de19d74a672cf522ecc_1704471097?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=qf0mR5MPHhk4RpamMO2GV4BtFOU%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Why is there not always free Wi-Fi on planes?  I mean its 2024. Why is airline technology so far behind? The lack of free Wi-Fi on airplanes in 2024 is due to both financial incentives for airlines and technical limitations. To offer Wi-Fi, planes require antennas, a network modem, and wireless access points, with retrofitting existing aircraft being expensive and time-consuming.  Wi-Fi connectivity is achieved either through satellite antennas or air-to-ground (ATG) antennas. ATG antennas face challenges over large bodies of water, leading to reliance on satellite Wi-Fi, which uses orbiting satellites for data transmission, ensuring continuous connectivity. Airlines often use a hybrid of both systems. While charging for Wi-Fi does generate extra revenue for airlines, it also manages bandwidth limitations.  With potentially hundreds of passengers wanting to use the service, making it free would overwhelm the limited bandwidth, degrading the quality for everyone.  Hence, airlines charge for Wi-Fi to limit the number of users and maintain service quality.  #techtok #technology #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/e66620df16584dfea3a6dfbcaec2b42f_1704312928?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=4HGvLPLkMIfleG%2BJNZ6%2BEqlRT6w%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/e66620df16584dfea3a6dfbcaec2b42f_1704312928?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=4HGvLPLkMIfleG%2BJNZ6%2BEqlRT6w%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/e66620df16584dfea3a6dfbcaec2b42f_1704312928?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=4HGvLPLkMIfleG%2BJNZ6%2BEqlRT6w%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Who invented Wi-Fi? And how does it work? Hedy Lamarr was an Austrian-American actress and inventor who pioneered the technology that would one day form the basis for today's WiFi, GPS, and Bluetooth communication systems. While many people and organizations were involved, the person who contributed the most to the WiFi we know today is Vic Hayes. Many consider Hayes, who invented WiFi and call him â€œthe father of WiFi.â€ Wi-Fi 6, also known as 802.11ax, is the latest generation of Wi-Fi technology, succeeding Wi-Fi 5 (802.11ac).  2.4 GHz is better for longer-range and compatibility but faces more interference and offers slower speeds. 5 GHz provides faster speeds and less interference but has a shorter range and requires more modern devices. 6 GHz (Wi-Fi 6E) offers the highest speeds and least interference but is limited in terms of device compatibility and range. #tech #techtok #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/1a6a7a2c557447f689e5bb4e1898d64f_1703806900~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oQI0HjELfHcDeFsbuuED2gAIS3CfAwhAwQAnEA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2Bjy3f2%2Fr%2BFal6SI1%2B5b0N1MaTp8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/1a6a7a2c557447f689e5bb4e1898d64f_1703806900~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oQI0HjELfHcDeFsbuuED2gAIS3CfAwhAwQAnEA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2Bjy3f2%2Fr%2BFal6SI1%2B5b0N1MaTp8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/1a6a7a2c557447f689e5bb4e1898d64f_1703806900~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oQI0HjELfHcDeFsbuuED2gAIS3CfAwhAwQAnEA.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=%2Bjy3f2%2Fr%2BFal6SI1%2B5b0N1MaTp8%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

It all boils down to binary code, the language of computers! Imagine light switches: on is 1, off is 0. <img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What is a JWT (JSON Web Token)? It is a sophisticated framework for authentication and information exchange. Encoded as a JSON object, it's structured in three parts: Header, Payload, and Signature. It's not just a token, it's a compact, URL-safe vessel carrying digitally signed data that can verify itself. Ideal for single sign-ons and bearer token patterns, JWTs are the linchpins of modern secure web services.  #TechDeepDive #CyberSecurity #JSONWebToken " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oUaxRkiIEgoyLjufIoik359O9wEXACAbBA9IB3?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=tKHuIZ%2B7gDj5PyoPsZv%2Fwyf3NpM%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oUaxRkiIEgoyLjufIoik359O9wEXACAbBA9IB3?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=tKHuIZ%2B7gDj5PyoPsZv%2Fwyf3NpM%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oUaxRkiIEgoyLjufIoik359O9wEXACAbBA9IB3?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=tKHuIZ%2B7gDj5PyoPsZv%2Fwyf3NpM%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Chris Alan Lee çš„ Swear By It åˆ›ä½œçš„ How to make some extra cash working in tech ðŸ‘‡ Freelance Coding: Whether itâ€™s web development, app creation, or software solutions, your coding skills are in high demand. Tech Tutoring: Share your knowledge by tutoring coding, web development, or even basic computer skills.  Building and Selling Tech Tools: Develop useful tech tools or widgets and sell them online. Whether it's a productivity app, a unique WordPress plugin, or a new software tool, your innovation can turn into a steady income. Tech Blogging or Vlogging: Start a blog or YouTube channel focused on tech reviews, tutorials, or latest tech trends. Monetize through ads, sponsorships, or affiliate marketing. Participate in Paid Online Surveys or Beta Testing: Companies often pay for beta testing new products or for taking tech-focused surveys. Websites like UserTesting or BetaTesting can be a good start. Tech Consulting Services: If you have specialized knowledge, offer consulting services to businesses or startups. Hackathons:  Hackathon Aggregator Websites: Sites like Devpost, Hackathon.com, and Major League Hacking (MLH) are dedicated to listing various hackathons. These platforms allow you to filter events by location, date, and topic, making it easier to find one that suits your interests. University Websites: Many universities host hackathons and they often welcome participants from outside their student body. Check out the websites of tech-focused universities like MIT, Stanford, or UC Berkeley." fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/457609efbbf4490fa02a19412e10aace_1700777336?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=ipCnWXbmfPOZCCDMTo5bkri0NTQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/457609efbbf4490fa02a19412e10aace_1700777336?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=ipCnWXbmfPOZCCDMTo5bkri0NTQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/457609efbbf4490fa02a19412e10aace_1700777336?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=ipCnWXbmfPOZCCDMTo5bkri0NTQ%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ This is forever my roman empire.  What is quantum computing? ðŸ‘‡ Quantum computing is an advanced computing technology that leverages the principles of quantum mechanics, using qubits that can exist in multiple states simultaneously, unlike traditional bits in classical computers. This unique capability allows quantum computers to perform complex calculations, such as factoring large numbers, much faster than conventional computers. This speed poses a significant threat to current encryption methods, like RSA, which rely on the difficulty of these calculations for security. The potential of quantum computers to break these encryptions raises serious concerns about data security and privacy. In response, researchers are developing post-quantum cryptography, a new form of encryption believed to be secure against the capabilities of quantum computing, aiming to safeguard sensitive information in the impending quantum era. #tech #futuretech " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/40080f2810ac4fe2b9116ca99dd8282e_1700083223?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=qy12ep4c9v7I6W9nAdUit%2FXzXks%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/40080f2810ac4fe2b9116ca99dd8282e_1700083223?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=qy12ep4c9v7I6W9nAdUit%2FXzXks%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/40080f2810ac4fe2b9116ca99dd8282e_1700083223?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=qy12ep4c9v7I6W9nAdUit%2FXzXks%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ A DDoS attack is essentially a coordinated assault on the availability of a network service. It's executed by overwhelming the target - typically a web server - with a flood of internet traffic.  This traffic is not legitimate user requests; it's artificially generated and comes from many different sources, making it a &quot;distributed&quot; attack. Think of a server as a door through which your legitimate users need to pass. In a DDoS attack, this door is barraged by a huge crowd (traffic) that doesn't actually want to enter (non-legitimate requests); they just want to block the door so that the genuine users can't get through. From a technical perspective, this attack exploits the limited capacity of a network service. Servers have a finite amount of resources - like bandwidth, memory, and processing power. A DDoS attack saturates these resources. This means that real users' requests can't be processed, leading to service disruption or complete unavailability. #tech #techexpert #techexplained #coding #softwareengineer " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/okKKSjdVZCHIVALjtCfQCetCHnIygkeax8XGIK?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=QaQHEK5WzYQGgLPg6sn1NNDgvqI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/okKKSjdVZCHIVALjtCfQCetCHnIygkeax8XGIK?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=QaQHEK5WzYQGgLPg6sn1NNDgvqI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/okKKSjdVZCHIVALjtCfQCetCHnIygkeax8XGIK?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=QaQHEK5WzYQGgLPg6sn1NNDgvqI%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What is OAuth? OAuth (Open Authorization) is a standard for access delegation commonly used for token-based authentication and authorization. It allows third-party services to exchange your information without sharing your credentials. Hereâ€™s a simplified explanation with a real-world analogy: Imagine you have a safe deposit box at a bank, and the bank has a strict policy that only the owner of the safe deposit box (you) can access it with a key. Now, suppose you want your friend to retrieve some documents from your box. Authorization: Instead of giving your friend the key to your safe deposit box (which would be like sharing your password), you go to the bank and fill out some paperwork to give your friend permission to access your box. Token Exchange: The bank then gives your friend a one-time access token, a â€œvisitorâ€™s passâ€ of sorts. Access: Your friend uses this token to access your safe deposit box and retrieve the documents. They canâ€™t do anything else, like removing other items or peeking into someone elseâ€™s box. Limited Scope: The permission you gave is for a specific task and does not grant additional rights beyond what was needed for the task. Revocation: After the task is complete, the bank revokes the one-time access token, and your friend can no longer access your box unless you authorize them again. #tech #techexplained #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/d7c7f2dc5cb94adb9ac8f64345924a2f_1698014758~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oMEAIJifaiVESWERhpNlWAFY4ACDyAQBAueF1C.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=eMYiNuEAv5RwYlynpr%2BpFPcJT04%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/d7c7f2dc5cb94adb9ac8f64345924a2f_1698014758~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oMEAIJifaiVESWERhpNlWAFY4ACDyAQBAueF1C.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=eMYiNuEAv5RwYlynpr%2BpFPcJT04%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/d7c7f2dc5cb94adb9ac8f64345924a2f_1698014758~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/oMEAIJifaiVESWERhpNlWAFY4ACDyAQBAueF1C.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=eMYiNuEAv5RwYlynpr%2BpFPcJT04%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Many people use the terms SDK and API interchangeably, but they actually refer to different things. An API (Application Programming Interface) allows two software programs to communicate with each other. It defines a set of functions and protocols for building software applications. For example, the Instagram API allows developers to access Instagram data and build apps that interact with the Instagram platform. An SDK (Software Development Kit) is a collection of tools that allows developers to build applications for a specific platform, like iOS or Android. The SDK includes API libraries/interfaces, documentation, code samples, processes etc. Basically, it provides everything a developer needs to start building apps for that platform. The Instagram SDK contains the Instagram API as well as libraries, code samples and guides specifically for building Instagram integrated apps for iOS, Android, Web etc. So the Instagram SDK is built on top of the Instagram API. In summary: API is the interface for communicating between software programs SDK is a complete package for building apps on a platform using its APIs So APIs provide the core communication while SDKs provide additional tools and libraries around those APIs for easier development. #tech #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oghItyImOMtF3gzNAoNDfLAkB0ECrcCqg1kyuC~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/o81kztOYCh1EIruVXAyofBWmEpI1AAEmAgFAD9.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=smnIZ4beYqPle6S8VSOTVNVvBvw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oghItyImOMtF3gzNAoNDfLAkB0ECrcCqg1kyuC~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/o81kztOYCh1EIruVXAyofBWmEpI1AAEmAgFAD9.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=smnIZ4beYqPle6S8VSOTVNVvBvw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/oghItyImOMtF3gzNAoNDfLAkB0ECrcCqg1kyuC~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/o81kztOYCh1EIruVXAyofBWmEpI1AAEmAgFAD9.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=smnIZ4beYqPle6S8VSOTVNVvBvw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Anderson .Paak çš„ Make It Better (Instrumental) åˆ›ä½œçš„ Getting real-world coding experience (or other skills) can be tough when you're just starting out. But here's a tip - use your network of friends and family! Offer to build websites, apps, or automate tasks for them. Not only will you get invaluable practice, but you'll also have real projects for your portfolio. When it comes time for interviews, share how you took initiative and solved problems for people you know. Talk about how you had to scope out requirements, wear multiple hats, and manage projects end-to-end. These &quot;freelance&quot; experiences show you have initiative, hunger to learn, and ability to deliver. The bottom line is don't wait around for the perfect coding job to gain experience. Take advantage of opportunities in your existing network. Build real things for real people. Develop your skills. <img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Sabrina Carpenter çš„ Feather - Sped Up åˆ›ä½œçš„ Get readh &amp; talk tech: startup vs. big tech edition. ðŸ‘‡ Base Salary: This is the regular, fixed amount of money you get paid by your employer for doing your job. It's usually expressed as an annual figure but paid out monthly or bi-weekly. Equity: Equity is like getting a tiny slice of the company pie. It represents a share of ownership in the company. If the company does well, the value of your slice can grow. Stock: Stock is a specific form of equity. It represents actual shares or pieces of the company that you own. If you have stock in a company, you own a part of that company, and you might make money if the company does well, usually through selling the stock at a higher price or through dividends (a share of the company's profits). In a nutshell, base salary is your regular pay, equity is a share of the ownership in the company, and stock is a specific form of that ownership. #tech #salary #TechTrends " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/b4a41cc1727c4aa09e1264cb945504db_1696203122~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ow5e0ECMItRJAFAvhbR70QgSltAAqneTGADQAB.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=tMNXy2ZbWgYk0x%2FVNFQu2y3j6Aw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/b4a41cc1727c4aa09e1264cb945504db_1696203122~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ow5e0ECMItRJAFAvhbR70QgSltAAqneTGADQAB.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=tMNXy2ZbWgYk0x%2FVNFQu2y3j6Aw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/b4a41cc1727c4aa09e1264cb945504db_1696203122~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/ow5e0ECMItRJAFAvhbR70QgSltAAqneTGADQAB.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=tMNXy2ZbWgYk0x%2FVNFQu2y3j6Aw%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Have you ever wanted to get ahead by predicting the future?The famed sci-fi writer predicted tablets, smart homes, and space stations decades before they existed! ðŸ¤¯ The remarkable Arthur C. Clarke was not only a brilliant science fiction writer, but a visionary futurist. Clarke foresaw many technological advances decades before they became reality. Among his forecasts that have come to pass are communications satellites, computer tablets, video calls, and space stations. He envisioned the internet long before it existed and described a worldwide communications network eerily similar to the real thing. Some of Clarke's predictions have yet to materialize but still could someday. He envisioned a future where we could grow or clone replacement organs, control the weather, harness the power of the sun, develop artificial intelligence superior to humans, and make contact with extraterrestrial life. <img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Microservices is an architectural approach in software development where an application is built as a collection of small, independent services.  Let's take an e-commerce platform as an example. Instead of one large application, it's broken down into separate services like User Management, Product Catalog, Shopping Cart, Payment, and Order Management.  Each service handles a specific business capability and communicates through APIs. With microservices, teams can work independently on each service, using different technologies if needed. They can scale and update services individually, resulting in better scalability, flexibility, and maintainability.  For example, during peak shopping seasons, the Product Catalog and Shopping Cart services can scale independently to handle increased traffic. However, it also introduces complexities like service communication and data consistency. Overall, microservices enable faster development, easier maintenance, and resilience by avoiding the dependence on a single large application. #tech #techexplained #learnontiktok #futuretech #techtok #stem " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/f2a58b6eb10c422b92ef6bb5b8f88e51_1685305054~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/1c3e9e7b3f4346d4ab634c3b669eb218.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=2HnobrPktCE2p5MEdsz87u9hS5w%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/f2a58b6eb10c422b92ef6bb5b8f88e51_1685305054~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/1c3e9e7b3f4346d4ab634c3b669eb218.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=2HnobrPktCE2p5MEdsz87u9hS5w%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/f2a58b6eb10c422b92ef6bb5b8f88e51_1685305054~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/1c3e9e7b3f4346d4ab634c3b669eb218.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=2HnobrPktCE2p5MEdsz87u9hS5w%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ What is a prompt engineer and how do you become one? Sharing some courses in the video as well!  Think of a &quot;prompt engineer&quot; like a teacher for artificial intelligence (AI). You know how when you're learning something new, a teacher might give you a problem or a question (a &quot;prompt&quot;) to help you understand? A prompt engineer does the same thing, but for AI. They design and create these prompts to teach the AI how to respond. For example, if you're using a voice assistant and you ask, &quot;What's the weather like today?&quot;, the AI knows how to respond correctly because a prompt engineer helped train it on this type of question. So essentially, a prompt engineer is someone who trains AI models to better understand and respond to different inputs or questions from users. They play a crucial role in making our interactions with AI more effective and natural. #promptengineering #chatgpt #ai #tech #techtok " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/o8GkFYEeTA3hBR8gQE8fcAJnhbAP4iADBEBFwI~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/6aa3cbd397324bd08b83a68f00d39306.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=kmZERybtKgQT%2FNe%2BfVF2XPLpkig%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/o8GkFYEeTA3hBR8gQE8fcAJnhbAP4iADBEBFwI~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/6aa3cbd397324bd08b83a68f00d39306.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=kmZERybtKgQT%2FNe%2BfVF2XPLpkig%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-p-0068/o8GkFYEeTA3hBR8gQE8fcAJnhbAP4iADBEBFwI~tplv-dmt-logom:tos-useast2a-v-0068/6aa3cbd397324bd08b83a68f00d39306.image?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=kmZERybtKgQT%2FNe%2BfVF2XPLpkig%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ DevOps is about uniting development and IT operations teams for faster and more reliable software delivery. Imagine an e-commerce company. Before DevOps, the developers wrote code and then handed it off to operations for deployment. Issues often arose in this siloed approach, leading to blame games between the teams. With DevOps, these teams work together from the start, sharing responsibilities. Automation is a cornerstone, including automated testing and deployment, known as CI/CD. Monitoring tools quickly detect production issues, often resolving them before users notice. And crucially, feedback loops ensure that any problems found in production are swiftly communicated back to developers. So, DevOps speeds up development cycles, reduces deployment failures, quickens recovery from failure, and boosts team collaboration, allowing businesses to deliver improvements more rapidly and with less risk. #developer #tech #techexpert #techexplained " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/847f8d5d381a486bacd50ab2ab3e8d24_1684954855?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=SVCuOUjfh6m1aGbXdj7CZSrO27c%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/847f8d5d381a486bacd50ab2ab3e8d24_1684954855?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=SVCuOUjfh6m1aGbXdj7CZSrO27c%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/847f8d5d381a486bacd50ab2ab3e8d24_1684954855?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=SVCuOUjfh6m1aGbXdj7CZSrO27c%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Save this for your next tech interview or when you are in a meeting and someone brings up CI/CD.  CI/CD stands for Continuous Integration and Continuous Deployment. It is a software development approach that focuses on frequent and automated code testing, building, and deployment to ensure high-quality and reliable software. In simpler terms, CI/CD is a process of continuously integrating changes to the codebase, automatically testing those changes, and then deploying them to production as soon as possible. For example, consider a software development team working on a mobile application. With CI/CD, every time a developer makes a change to the code, the change is automatically integrated with the rest of the codebase, and tests are run to ensure that the new code doesn't break any existing functionality. If the tests pass, the new code is automatically deployed to a staging environment where it can be further tested. If the code passes all tests and meets the requirements, it is then automatically deployed to production. #techtok #techexplained #stem  " fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oc1oIfAIkzy4GiCwvoYRAYCoEtZ2K9ghFEIvtB?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=H%2BwY6Fnsb0LTwtKHTUyf%2BoB1BEE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=-" imagex-type="react" imagex-version="0.3.10" srcset="https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oc1oIfAIkzy4GiCwvoYRAYCoEtZ2K9ghFEIvtB?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=H%2BwY6Fnsb0LTwtKHTUyf%2BoB1BEE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 1x, https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/oc1oIfAIkzy4GiCwvoYRAYCoEtZ2K9ghFEIvtB?lk3s=81f88b70&amp;x-expires=1748566800&amp;x-signature=H%2BwY6Fnsb0LTwtKHTUyf%2BoB1BEE%3D&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=- 2x" style="position: absolute; inset: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; border: none; margin: auto; display: block; width: 0px; height: 0px; min-width: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; max-height: 100%;">

<img alt="Tiff in Tech ä½¿ç”¨ Tiff in Tech çš„ original sound åˆ›ä½œçš„ Save this for your next tech interview or when youre in a meeting and someone brings up proxy. The simple example in the video really helped me get it.  A proxy server is a tool that can be used to enhance security, bypass censorship, and improve performance. By acting as an intermediary between clients and the internet, a proxy server can mask a client's IP address from the destination server, making it difficult for the destination server to track or monitor activity. It can also be used to access content that may be restricted in certain locations by bypassing internet censorship. Additionally, proxies can help optimize online resources by caching frequently requested content and reducing load on the destination server. There are several types of proxy servers available including HTTP proxies, SOCKS proxies, transparent proxies and reverse proxies; each type has different features and applications. For example, HTTP proxies are often used to access websites while SOCKS proxies provide more versatile support for other network protocols.
